      • getTarget

        public String getTarget()
        Description copied from interface: IMXMLInstructionData
        Returns the target of the processing instruction.

        The target is the identifier that follows the <?. For example, for <?foo bar baz?> the target is "foo".

        Specified by:
        getTarget in interface IMXMLInstructionData

      • getContent

        public String getContent()
        Description copied from interface: IMXMLInstructionData
        Returns the content of the processing instruction.

        The content is everything that follows the whitespace after the target, up to the ?>. For example, for <?foo bar baz?> the content is "bar baz".

        Specified by:
        getContent in interface IMXMLInstructionData
